<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0">
    <teiHeader><fileDesc><titleStmt><title>The Ambassador in Iran (
                        Allen
                    ) to the Secretary of
                            State</title></titleStmt><sourceDesc><bibl type="frus-volume-id">frus1946v07</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-id">d364</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-number">364</bibl><bibl type="frus-div-subtype">historical-document</bibl></sourceDesc></fileDesc><profileDesc><settingDesc><setting><date notBefore="1946-05-28T01:30:00-05:00" notAfter="1946-05-28T01:30:00-05:00"/></setting></settingDesc></profileDesc></teiHeader><text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1946-05-28T01:30:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1946-05-28T01:30:00-05:00" n="364" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d364">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">891.00/5–2846: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Iran</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Allen</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">us urgent</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tehran</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1946-05-28T10:00:00+03:30">May 28, 1946—10 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 3:57 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>762. <gloss target="#t_Deptel1">Deptel</gloss> 464, May 25. Ward saw Qavam last
                    night and conveyed Dept’s views that withdrawal of Ala’s letter of May 20 to
                        <gloss target="#t_SC1">SC</gloss> would be unfortunate.</p>
                <p>He did not indicate that Ala had approached Dept but rather explained our
                    interest on basis of Qavam’s remarks to Ambassador as reported <gloss target="#t_Embtel1">Embtel</gloss> May 25.<note n="56" xml:id="d364fn56">Telegram 750, <ref target="#pg_480">p. 480</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_PriMin1">PriMin</gloss> said Ala had disregarded instructions
                    to withdraw letter and apparently had no intention of withdrawing it. It
                    appeared from his remarks that Qavam does not plan to pursue matter further,
                    although he is apprehensive Soviet Ambassador may continue to press for
                    withdrawal.</p>
                <p>He asserted he was very anxious not to weaken Iran’s position before UN and
                    wished to maintain good will and sympathy of American Government and people
                    toward Iran.</p>
                <p>Qavam said Ala had been ordered return Washington. If Iran should need
                    representative to appear again before <gloss target="#t_SC1">SC</gloss>, new one
                    would be designated.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Allen</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
